    <legis-type>A BILL</legis-type>
    <official-title>To repeal the Act of May 31, 1918, and for other purposes.</official-title>
  </form>
  <legis-body>
    <section id="idD3A7739F6347412AB822D7EB36A901DA" section-type="section-one">
      <enum>1.</enum>
      <header>Short title</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the <quote>
          <short-title>
            <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="May 31, 1918 Act Repeal Act" proposed="true">May 31, 1918 Act Repeal Act</cato:entity-ref>
          </short-title>
        </quote>.</text>
    </section>
    <section id="idF49EDC0A605E44C284FEE266F80968E7">
      <enum>2.</enum>
      <header>Definitions</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">In this Act:</text>
      <paragraph id="id95A99B59F1AA4F54B6D8A8AB6D3D3010">
        <enum>(1)</enum>
        <header>1918 Act</header>
        <text>The term <term>1918 Act</term> means the Act of May 31, 1918 (<cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="statute-at-large" value="statute-at-large/40/592">40 Stat. 592</cato:entity-ref>, chapter 88).</text>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph id="id7BF21A8B7ACA41109EA8D10C13D98FFD">
        <enum>(2)</enum>
        <header>Tribes</header>
        <text>The term <term>Tribes</term> means the Shoshone-Bannock Tribes of the Fort Hall Indian Reservation.</text>
      </paragraph>
    </section>
    <section id="idEDA882DFA7694727BA63995B410B4A78">
      <enum>3.</enum>
      <header>Repeal</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">The 1918 Act is repealed.</text>
    </section>
    <section id="idDAC0A692D1CC4710A980A72E46A74C00">
      <enum>4.</enum>
      <header>Right of first refusal</header>
      <subsection id="id337B8B9C36BE4678976E1C7910FE91EC">
        <enum>(a)</enum>
        <header>In general</header>
        <text>The Tribes shall have the exclusive right of first refusal to purchase at fair market value any
			 land—</text>
        <paragraph id="id084AB3806C854C3290451978A2E2B19E">
          <enum>(1)</enum>
          <text>set aside or set apart under the 1918 Act; and</text>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="id62CA6BF489AA4AF7B254961B72430BC5">
          <enum>(2)</enum>
          <text>offered for sale.</text>
        </paragraph>
      </subsection>
      <subsection id="idF0C543F7D7364D69A951854698F066DE">
        <enum>(b)</enum>
        <header>Acquired land held in trust</header>
        <text>The United States shall hold in
			 trust for the benefit of the Tribes or a member of the Tribes, as
			 applicable—</text>
        <paragraph id="id7426227704BE4D27BD6A33924F229DBA">
          <enum>(1)</enum>
          <text>any land acquired by the Tribes or a member of the Tribes before the date of enactment of this Act;
			 and</text>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="id2DE4D5A6DC794E349FAFEFA775A72E08">
          <enum>(2)</enum>
          <text>any land—</text>
          <subparagraph id="idFDF4433BAF4F4A85BA32D0852DD9ED6C">
            <enum>(A)</enum>
            <text>acquired by the Tribes or a member of the Tribes on or after the date of enactment of this Act; and</text>
          </subparagraph>
          <subparagraph id="id61BF564D862D4DD981D9F7E0723541A4">
            <enum>(B)</enum>
            <text>set aside or set apart under the 1918 Act.</text>
          </subparagraph>
        </paragraph>
      </subsection>
    </section>
    <section id="id6E13408CE88A474EB4B17EDCD9E73711">
      <enum>5.</enum>
      <header>Effect</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">Nothing in this Act affects any valid right to any land set aside or set apart under the 1918 Act.</text>
    </section>
  </legis-body>
